  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Current state: 0% coverage.** No `tests/` directory, no `pytest.ini`/`pyproject.toml`, no test dependencies in `requirements.txt`. Every function below is untested. I've prioritized by risk (parsers that break silently on upstream API changes, retry/pagination logic, dedup correctness) and given skeletons for representative cases rather than all ~25 near-identical ATS parsers.\n\n**Suggested setup** (not currently present):\n```\nrequirements-dev.txt: pytest, pytest-asyncio, freezegun\n```\n`httpx.MockTransport` covers all async HTTP mocking needs — no need for `respx`.\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` — highest-value target, pure logic, currently silent about a real gap\n\n**Untested:** `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`\n\n**Edge cases not covered:**\n- Epoch milliseconds (Lever) vs epoch seconds — the `>= 1e12` heuristic branch\n- ISO-8601 with trailing `Z`, with explicit offset, naive (no tz) — falls into `.replace(tzinfo=utc)`\n- **Workday's prose format** (`\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"`) — this is neither digit nor ISO, so it silently returns `None`. That means the `max_age_days` filter never actually excludes stale Workday postings (filters.py explicitly *keeps* unparseable dates). This is a real, currently-invisible behavior gap worth a regression test.\n- Empty string / `None` input\n- Negative-looking numeric string (`\"-5\"` — `lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()` accepts it) → nonsensical date, not currently guarded\n- `content_hash` stability: identical title/location/url/department → identical hash regardless of other fields (raw, posted_at) changing\n- `key` uniqueness/stability across title edits\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds_lever(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332430\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1643241332\")\n        assert dt.year == 2022\n\n    def test_iso8601_with_z_suffix(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\").tzinfo is not None\n\n    def test_iso8601_naive_gets_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_workday_prose_is_unparseable(self):\n        # documents current behavior: recency filter can't act on Workday dates\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value\", [\"\", None])\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self, value):\n        assert parse_posted_at(value) is None\n\n    def test_garbage_string_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not a date\") is None\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **overrides):\n        base = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                     title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x\", location=\"NYC\",\n                     department=\"Eng\")\n        return Job(**{**base, **overrides})\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_composite(self):\n        assert self._job().key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_content_hash_ignores_raw_and_posted_at(self):\n        a = self._job(raw={\"x\": 1}, posted_at=\"2024-01-01\")\n        b = self._job(raw={\"x\": 2}, posted_at=\"2024-06-01\")\n        assert a.content_hash == b.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title_edit(self):\n        a = self._job()\n        b = self._job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")\n        assert a.content_hash != b.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_includes_key_and_hash(self):\n        row = self._job(raw={\"secret\": 1}).to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] and row[\"content_hash\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py`\n\n**Untested:** `match`, `filter_jobs`, `_compile`\n\n**Edge cases:**\n- Word-boundary regex: `\"eng\"` in include list must NOT match `\"Engineering\"` (only whole word) — verify `\\b` behavior isn't accidentally substring matching\n- `exclude` takes precedence over `include` when both match\n- Empty/`None` include/exclude/locations lists → no filtering applied\n- `locations` is substring/case-insensitive match, not exact\n- Cutoff: job with **unparseable** `posted_at` must survive the cutoff filter (documented \"keep\" behavior) — pairs with the Workday gap above\n- Cutoff: job exactly at the boundary\n- `filter_jobs` with `max_age_days` as string in config (yaml loose typing) — `float(max_age)` coercion\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef _job(title=\"Software Engineer\", dept=\"\", loc=\"\", posted_at=\"\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=title,\n               url=\"u\", department=dept, location=loc, posted_at=posted_at)\n\ndef test_include_whole_word_not_substring():\n    # \"eng\" should not match \"Engineering\" as a substring\n    assert match(_job(title=\"Engineering Manager\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is False\n    assert match(_job(title=\"Eng Manager\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is True\n\ndef test_exclude_overrides_include():\n    j = _job(title=\"Senior Manager\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"manager\"], exclude=[\"senior\"]) is False\n\ndef test_locations_case_insensitive_substring():\n    j = _job(loc=\"New York, NY\")\n    assert match(j, locations=[\"new york\"]) is True\n\ndef test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_dates():\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    j = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")  # unparseable\n    assert match(j, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\ndef test_cutoff_drops_old_parseable_dates():\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n    old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=5)).isoformat()\n    assert match(_job(posted_at=old), cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_max_age_days_as_string_from_yaml():\n    jobs = [_job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())]\n    result = filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": \"30\"})\n    assert len(result) == 1\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` — dedup correctness is the core value proposition of this app; untested entirely\n\n**Untested:** `Store.__init__`, `_migrate`, `diff`, `_insert`, `_update`, `get_meta`/`set_meta`, `added_since`, `count`\n\n**Edge cases / gaps:**\n- Fresh DB creates schema correctly\n- **Migration path**: opening a DB created before `salary_range` existed doesn't crash (needs a fixture pre-populating an old-shape table)\n- `diff()`: new job → inserted, appears in `new`\n- `diff()`: same key + same `content_hash` → appears in neither list, but `last_seen` is bumped\n- `diff()`: same key + different `content_hash` → appears in `changed`, row updated\n- `diff()` with empty list → no-op, no crash\n- `added_since` ordering (first_seen, company, title) and strict `>` boundary (a row with `first_seen == ts` must be excluded)\n- `set_meta` upsert (insert then update same key)\n- Context manager closes connection\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n                title=title, url=\"u\", location=\"NYC\")\n\ndef test_new_job_is_inserted_and_reported_new(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n    assert store.count() == 1\n\ndef test_unchanged_job_reported_in_neither_list(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert new == [] and changed == []\n\ndef test_content_change_reported_as_changed_not_new(store):\n    store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n    assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\ndef test_migration_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_db(tmp_path):\n    import sqlite3\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.execute(\"\"\"CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT,\n        company TEXT, external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n        department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n        content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT)\"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\ndef test_added_since_excludes_exact_boundary(store, monkeypatch):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n    assert store.added_since(ts) == []  # strictly-after semantics\n\ndef test_meta_upsert(store):\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n    assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\ndef test_get_meta_missing_key_returns_none(store):\n    assert store.get_meta(\"nope\") is None\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `pipeline.py` — no integration test exists for the full orchestration path\n\n**Untested:** `load_config` defaults, `run` (dry-run and normal), `run_sync`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport pipeline\n\ndef test_load_config_applies_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_file = tmp_path / \"min.yaml\"\n    cfg_file.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_file)\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_does_not_touch_store_or_notify(tmp_path):\n    cfg_file = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_file.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path/'x.db'}\\n\")\n    with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.Store\") as MockStore, \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_file, dry_run=True)\n    MockStore.assert_not_called()\n    mock_dispatch.assert_not_called()\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_dispatches_new_and_changed(tmp_path):\n    from models import Job\n    j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"E\", url=\"u\")\n    cfg_file = tmp_path / \"c.yaml\"\n    cfg_file.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path/'x.db'}\\n\")\n    with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", AsyncMock(return_value=[j])), \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_file, dry_run=False)\n    assert result[\"new\"] == 1\n    mock_dispatch.assert_called_once()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `notify.py`\n\n**Untested:** all five notifiers + `dispatch`\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `dispatch` fault isolation — **this is the one behavior most worth locking down**: one notifier raising must not block the rest\n- Each conditional notifier is a no-op when its env var(s) are unset, and a no-op when there's nothing to report even if configured\n- `notify_sms`: truncation at `limit=8`, ASCII-only body, `raise_for_status` propagates on Twilio auth failure (caught by `dispatch`, not by the notifier itself)\n- `notify_email`: SMTP interaction needs mocking (`smtplib.SMTP`), optional auth branch (`SMTP_USER` set vs unset)\n- `notify_webhook`/`notify_slack`: payload shape assertions\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nimport notify\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef _job(title=\"Engineer\", company=\"Acme\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=company, external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\")\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_notifier_failures(capsys):\n    with patch.object(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [\n        MagicMock(side_effect=RuntimeError(\"boom\"), __name__=\"broken\"),\n        (ok := MagicMock(__name__=\"ok\")),\n    ]):\n        notify.dispatch([_job()], [])\n    ok.assert_called_once()\n    assert \"broken\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_env(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n    post.assert_not_called()\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_when_nothing_new(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.example/x\")\n    with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\") as post:\n        notify.notify_slack([], [])\n    post.assert_not_called()\n\ndef test_sms_body_truncates_and_is_ascii():\n    jobs = [_job(title=f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(12)]\n    body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [])\n    assert \"+4 more\" in body\n    assert body.isascii()\n\ndef test_notify_sms_raises_on_twilio_failure_propagates_to_dispatch(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    for k, v in [(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\"), (\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", \"tok\"),\n                 (\"TWILIO_FROM\", \"+1\"), (\"TWILIO_TO\", \"+2\")]:\n        monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n    resp = MagicMock()\n    resp.raise_for_status.side_effect = Exception(\"401 unauthorized\")\n    with patch(\"notify.httpx.post\", return_value=resp):\n        notify.dispatch([_job()], [])  # must not raise out of dispatch\n    assert \"notify_sms failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `fetchers.py` — largest surface area, highest breakage risk (upstream API drift), zero coverage\n\n#### 6a. Retry/backoff — `_request` — **has an untested bug-shaped edge case**\n`raise_for_status()` raises `HTTPStatusError` for *any* 4xx/5xx, and that's caught by the same `except` that handles the \"retryable\" statuses — meaning a permanent `404` currently gets retried the full `retries` times identically to a `503`, burning ~30s of backoff on something that will never succeed. Worth a test that pins down current behavior (and flags it as a candidate fix).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_request.py\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import _request\n\ndef _client(handler):\n    return httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] < 3:\n            return httpx.Response(503)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"ok\": True})\n    async with _client(handler) as c:\n        r = await _request(c, \"https://x/y\", retries=4)\n    assert r.status_code == 200 and calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_exhausts_retries_and_raises_runtime_error():\n    async def handler(request): return httpx.Response(503)\n    async with _client(handler) as c:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(c, \"https://x/y\", retries=2)\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_404_currently_also_gets_retried(monkeypatch):\n    # documents current (likely unintended) behavior — 404 is not distinguished\n    # from a transient 503 and burns the full retry budget.\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(404)\n    async with _client(handler) as c:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(c, \"https://x/y\", retries=3)\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 3\n```\n\n#### 6b. Parsers — need coverage for every `parse_*`, prioritized by fragility\n\nFull defensive/bespoke parsers (regex- or positional-index-based, most likely to silently degrade on a layout change) matter most: `parse_google`/`_extract_ds1`/`_ds1_posted_at`, `parse_deshaw`, `parse_twosigma`, `_amazon_posted_at`. Representative skeletons:\n\n```python\n# tests/test_parsers.py\nfrom fetchers import (parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary,\n                       parse_google, _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at,\n                       parse_deshaw, _amazon_posted_at, parse_amazon)\n\nclass TestGreenhouse:\n    def test_maps_fields(self):\n        data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"SWE\",\n                           \"absolute_url\": \"https://x/1\",\n                           \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"},\n                           \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Eng\"}, {\"name\": \"Core\"}],\n                           \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"}]}\n        [j] = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n        assert j.department == \"Eng, Core\"\n        assert j.location == \"NYC\"\n\n    def test_empty_jobs_list(self):\n        assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n    def test_missing_optional_fields_dont_crash(self):\n        [j] = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1}]})\n        assert j.title == \"\" and j.location == \"\"\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_range_with_currency(self):\n        j = {\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"USD 100,000–150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_plain_description(self):\n        j = {\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n        assert _lever_salary(j) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_no_salary_info_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\nclass TestGoogleDs1:\n    def test_extract_ds1_happy_path(self):\n        html = \"before key: 'ds:1', ..., data:[[[\\\"a\\\"]]] , sideChannel:{} after\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == [[\"a\"]]\n\n    def test_extract_ds1_missing_blob_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_extract_ds1_malformed_json_returns_empty(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', data:[[not json]] , sideChannel:{}\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) == []\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_prefers_create_time_index_12(self):\n        job = [None] * 15\n        job[12] = [1700000000]\n        job[13] = [1800000000]\n        assert _ds1_posted_at(job) != \"\"\n        assert \"2023\" in _ds1_posted_at(job)  # create-time, not update-time\n\n    def test_ds1_posted_at_missing_all_indices(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([None] * 5) == \"\"\n\n    def test_parse_google_skips_falsy_id_entries(self):\n        assert parse_google(\"google\", [None, [0], []]) == []\n\nclass TestDeshaw:\n    def test_dedups_repeated_cards(self):\n        page = ('<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">SWE</span>'\n                '<span class=\"location\">NYC</span></div>'\n                '<div data-job-id=\"1\"><span class=\"job-display-name\">SWE</span></div>')\n        out = parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page)\n        assert len(out) == 1\n\n    def test_skips_cards_missing_title(self):\n        page = '<div data-job-id=\"1\"></div>'\n        assert parse_deshaw(\"deshaw\", page) == []\n\nclass TestAmazonDate:\n    def test_valid_date_normalizes_to_iso(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_garbage_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_missing_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n```\n\n> **Note:** the same pattern (happy path + empty/missing input + malformed input) needs to be replicated for the currently-untested `parse_ashby`, `parse_smartrecruiters`, `parse_recruitee`, `parse_workable`, `parse_twosigma`, `parse_optiver`, `parse_meta`, `parse_microsoft`, `parse_netflix`, and the inline Workday posting mapping in `fetch_workday`. Each has at least one non-obvious normalization worth pinning (e.g. `parse_workable`'s dict-vs-flat `location` shape, `parse_netflix`'s comma-to-`\", \"` location respacing, `parse_recruitee`'s assembled-vs-flat location).\n\n#### 6c. Pagination loops — `fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_workday`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_meta`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`\n\n**Untested:** stop-on-empty-page termination, `max_pages` safety cap, dedup-via-`seen` across pages, correct offset/param increments.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetch_pagination.py\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_amazon\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_amazon_paginates_until_empty_page():\n    pages = [\n        {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\", \"job_path\": \"/a\"}]},\n        {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"2\", \"title\": \"B\", \"job_path\": \"/b\"}]},\n        {\"jobs\": []},\n    ]\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(request):\n        resp = httpx.Response(200, json=pages[calls[\"n\"]])\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return resp\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as c:\n        jobs = await fetch_amazon(c, {\"company\": \"amazon\"}, )  # client passed explicitly if signature allows\n    assert len(jobs) == 2 and calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_amazon_respects_max_pages_cap():\n    def handler(request):  # always returns a fresh id -> would loop forever\n        offset = int(request.url.params.get(\"offset\", 0))\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": str(offset), \"job_path\": \"/x\"}]})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as c:\n        jobs = await fetch_amazon(c, {\"company\": \"amazon\", \"max_pages\": 3})\n    assert len(jobs) == 3\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_amazon_dedups_repeated_ids_across_pages():\n    def handler(request):\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": [{\"id\": \"dup\", \"job_path\": \"/x\"}]})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as c:\n        jobs = await fetch_amazon(c, {\"company\": \"amazon\", \"max_pages\": 5})\n    assert len(jobs) == 0  # every page returns only the already-seen id -> stops immediately\n```\n*(Same shape applies to the other seven paginated fetchers — particularly `fetch_workday`'s `total`/`offset > 5000` safety-cap branch and `fetch_meta`'s single-POST-no-pagination path with the `graphql errors` → `RuntimeError` branch, both currently untested.)*\n\n#### 6d. `fetch_source` / `fetch_all` — orchestration\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetch_all.py\nimport httpx, pytest\nfrom fetchers import fetch_source, fetch_all\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_value_error():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as c:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(c, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_per_source_failures(capsys):\n    def handler(request):\n        if \"greenhouse\" in str(request.url):\n            return httpx.Response(500)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []})\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n    sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"broken\"},\n               {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"also-broken\"}]\n    jobs = await fetch_all(sources, client=client, concurrency=2)\n    assert jobs == []  # both failed but fetch_all didn't raise\n    assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_respects_concurrency_semaphore():\n    in_flight = {\"n\": 0, \"max\": 0}\n    async def handler(request):\n        in_flight[\"n\"] += 1\n        in_flight[\"max\"] = max(in_flight[\"max\"], in_flight[\"n\"])\n        import anyio; await anyio.sleep(0.01)\n        in_flight[\"n\"] -= 1\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []})\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n    sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": f\"c{i}\"} for i in range(10)]\n    await fetch_all(sources, client=client, concurrency=3)\n    assert in_flight[\"max\"] <= 3\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py`\n\n**Untested:** `cmd_db_new`, `cmd_db_mark`, `_normalize_ats`, `cmd_pdf_render`, `_chrome_bin`, `main` argv dispatch\n\n**Edge cases:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first run (no marker → default `FIRST_RUN_DAYS` window) vs marker present\n- `cmd_db_new`: truncation happens only at `first_seen` group boundaries, never splitting a batch — this is a subtle invariant worth a direct test\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now`, explicit watermark, invalid ISO string → exit code 2, neither arg supplied → exit code 2\n- `_normalize_ats`: replacements apply inside body text but **not** inside tags/`<style>`/`<script>` — needs a test proving an em-dash inside a `<script>` block is left untouched while one in a `<p>` is replaced\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file → exit 2; Chrome invocation success/failure via magic-byte check on output\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env override, `PATH` lookup, app-bundle fallback, none-found → `sys.exit`\n- `main`: mode-word vs flag-boundary splitting (`agent.py scan --foo` → mode_words=[\"scan\"], extra=[\"--foo\"]), bare invocation → interactive\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport pytest\nfrom agent import cmd_db_mark, _normalize_ats, cmd_db_new\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef test_db_mark_now(capsys):\n    assert cmd_db_mark([\"--now\"]) == 0\n\ndef test_db_mark_invalid_iso_exits_2(capsys):\n    assert cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\"]) == 2\n\ndef test_db_mark_no_args_exits_2():\n    assert cmd_db_mark([]) == 2\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_script_and_style_blocks():\n    html = \"<style>content: '\\u2014';</style><p>em\\u2014dash</p><script>'\\u2014'</script>\"\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert \"em-dash\" in out  # body replaced\n    assert \"content: '\\u2014'\" in out  # style untouched\n    assert \"'\\u2014'\" in out.split(\"<script>\")[1]  # script untouched\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_counts_all_replacement_types():\n    html = \"<p>a\\u2018b\\u2019c \\u2026 d\\u00a0e</p>\"\n    _, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert counts[\"smart-single-quote\"] == 2\n    assert counts[\"ellipsis\"] == 1\n    assert counts[\"nbsp\"] == 1\n\ndef test_db_new_truncates_only_at_group_boundary(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"db: {tmp_path/'j.db'}\\nsources: []\\n\")\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"j.db\") as s:\n        # two jobs share one first_seen batch (same pipeline run)\n        s.diff([Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=\"T\", url=\"u\")\n                 for i in range(5)])\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"agent.py\", \"db-new\", \"-c\", str(cfg), \"--limit\", \"2\"])\n    # with limit=2 but a 5-row group, expect either all-5 (group kept whole) or\n    # 0-with-truncated=True — never a partial 2-of-5 split\n    assert cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--limit\", \"2\"]) == 0\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `cli.py`\n\n**Untested:** argparse wiring end-to-end (thin, but currently zero coverage of the `--dry-run` flag actually reaching `run_sync`).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom cli import main\n\ndef test_dry_run_flag_passed_through(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"--dry-run\", \"-c\", \"x.yaml\"])\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        main()\n    mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"x.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Integration test gaps (no unit test substitutes for these)\n\n1. **End-to-end pipeline run** against a `Store` backed by a real temp SQLite file plus a mocked `httpx` transport for one real fetcher (e.g. greenhouse) — verifies fetch → filter → dedup → notify wiring end to end, not just each stage mocked out.\n2. **Two consecutive pipeline runs** against the same DB: first run reports everything as `new`, second run with one changed title reports it as `changed` and the rest as neither — proves `store.diff` integration holds across a realistic scan/rescan cycle.\n3. **`agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` → `db-new` cycle**: verifies the watermark-not-`--now` guidance in the docstring actually prevents skipping rows landing mid-analysis.\n4. **`sources.yaml` schema validation**: no test currently loads the real `sources.yaml` through `load_config` + `fetch_source` to confirm every configured entry's `ats` key resolves to a registered fetcher (would catch a typo'd `ats:` value before a scheduled run silently drops a whole company).\n\n---\n\nWant me to actually scaffold these as real files under a `tests/` directory (with `conftest.py`, `pytest-asyncio` wired in, and `requirements-dev.txt`) rather than leave this as an analysis?\n",
