        "content": "\n**Untested:** `cmd_db_new`, `cmd_db_mark`, `_normalize_ats`, `cmd_pdf_render`, `_chrome_bin`, `main` argv dispatch\n\n**Edge cases:**\n- `cmd_db_new`: first run (no marker → default `FIRST_RUN_DAYS` window) vs marker present\n- `cmd_db_new`: truncation happens only at `first_seen` group boundaries, never splitting a batch — this is a subtle invariant worth a direct test\n- `cmd_db_mark`: `--now`, explicit watermark, invalid ISO string → exit code 2, neither arg supplied → exit code 2\n- `_normalize_ats`: replacements apply inside body text but **not** inside tags/`<style>`/`<script>` — needs a test proving an em-dash inside a `<script>` block is left untouched while one in a `<p>` is replaced\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file → exit 2; Chrome invocation success/failure via magic-byte check on output\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env override, `PATH` lookup, app-bundle fallback, none-found → `sys.exit`\n- `main`: mode-word vs flag-boundary splitting (`agent.py scan --foo` → mode_words=[\"scan\"], extra=[\"--foo\"]), bare invocation → interactive\n\n```python\n",
